body:
As mailbox.get() is blocking task call, there is no INFINITELOOP in the code below.


```verilog
class bfm;
 mailbox #(int) in_box;
 int tr;
   
 function new();
  this.in_box = new (1);
 endfunction : new

  task main();
      // /* verilator lint_off INFINITELOOP */
    forever begin : loop
      in_box.get(tr);
      $display("%0t BFM received XACTN via MAILBOX as: %0d",
        $time, tr);
      //#1;
    end : loop
  endtask : main
endclass : bfm

module m;

  bfm bfm_0;

  initial begin
    #10;
    bfm_0 = new();
    fork
      bfm_0.main();
    join_none

    bfm_0.in_box.put(10);
    #10;
    bfm_0.in_box.put(20);
    #10;
    bfm_0.in_box.put(30);
    #10;
    $finish (2);
  end
endmodule : m

```
But verilator does throw:
```log
%Warning-INFINITELOOP: mbx_get_lint.sv:11:5: Infinite loop (condition always true)
                                           : ... In instance m
   11 |     forever begin : loop
      |     ^~~~~~~
                       ... For warning description see https://verilator.org/warn/INFINITELOOP?v=5.013
                       ... Use "/* verilator lint_off INFINITELOOP */" and lint_on around source to disable this message.
```
